The figure shows an epicyclic gear train with gears A and B having 40 and 50 teeth, respectively. If the arm C rotates at 200 rpm in anticlockwise direction about the center of gear A which is fixed, then speed of revolution of gear B in rpm would be:
Two similar laminates are used in a chassis. The only difference is the core material. What is allowed?

answer_options.answer_text: Two different core materials are used with the same ply stacking. Testing the laminate with the core that has the highest shear strength and using the results for both panels is allowed to prove equivalency for both panels.

Two laminates are used with the same core and the ply stacking is doubled. Testing the laminate with the single ply stacking and using the result for both panels (using twice the thickness in the SES for the thicker laminate) is allowed to prove equivalency.

Two laminates with the same ply stacking and the core is doubled. Testing the laminate with the thicker core and using the results for both panels (using half the core thickness for the thinner laminate) is allowed to prove equivalency
